%I A397797 #9 Jul 13 2026 08:18:23
%S A397797 0,3,16,157,1707,25889
%N A397797 Number of free ouroboros polyknights with 2*n cells.
%C A397797 In analogy with the definition in A359706, an ouroboros polyknight is a polyknight in which every cell has exactly two neighbors.
%C A397797 There are no ouroboros polyknights with an odd number of cells.
%C A397797 Equivalently, a(n) is the number of induced cycles of length 2*n in the infinite knight graph, up to translations, rotations, and reflections.
%H A397797 Pontus von Brömssen, <a href="/A397797/a397797.svg">Illustration of all ouroboros polyknights with at most 6 cells</a>.
%H A397797 <a href="/index/Pol#polyominoes">Index entries for sequences related to polyominoes</a>.
%Y A397797 Cf. A030446, A165143, A297666, A359706.
%K A397797 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A397797 1,2
